HEADWORD: Femerell
<hw>Fem"er*ell</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>fumeraille</ets> part of a chimney. See <er>Fume</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A lantern, or louver covering, placed on a roof,
for ventilation or escape of smoke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

